02 Jun 2010 23:33






Oh good lord that's creepy. +1.

I'd like to use this article as an example, if you don't mind. It's a great instance of a quality I keep failing to explain adequately: the ability of a good write-up to transform a less-than-stellar premise. If I'd read just a brief summary of the effect itself, I'd have gone "okay, it's turning people into data and storing them in this Agent. Meh. What's the hook?" Suffice it to say that that was not my reaction upon reading the actual article… You imply so much in those logs. I love it.

My only suggestion would hinge on noting that not every reader of this article is even going to notice the log and interview, and therefore will miss most of the goodness. Is there any way you could hint at it a little more strongly in the main article's description or containment procedures? Some hint of what to do if someone or some other data disappears outright, for instance?








SCP Wiki Administrator  | Earth: We're all in this together.






